The paper deals with problems related to guarding polygonal domains in the plane, which is a classic problem in computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also provides upper and lower bounds on the number of guards required, which involves combinatorial and algorithmic techniques (cs.DS, cs.DM). The paper also discusses the construction of guard sets, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT).
